{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/simple calculator in javascript using MVC pattern","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"3c720f03-2c83-50fa-b258-d4854de885db","html":"<h1 id=\"what-i-want-to-do\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#what-i-want-to-do\" aria-label=\"what i want to do permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>What I want to do?</h1>\n<p>I want to write simple calculator app with plain JavaScript using Model-View-Controller design pattern.</p>\n<p>Check out <a href=\"https://gitsanto.github.io/SimpleCalculator_UsingMVCDesignPattern/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Demo</a></p>\n<h1 id=\"process\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#process\" aria-label=\"process permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Process</h1>\n<p>Creating 3 files only</p>\n<ul>\n<li>index.html : It consists of a single root element only in the body tag.</li>\n<li>style.css : It has styling for calculator.</li>\n<li>script.js : It consists of model, view and controller classes.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"what-the-heck-is-design-pattern\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#what-the-heck-is-design-pattern\" aria-label=\"what the heck is design pattern permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>What the heck is design pattern?</h2>\n<p>In programming world, programmers talk about things like singletons, mvc instead of basic terms like int, arrays. </p>\n<p>I not big fan of this but you will see many different design pattern used in software applications.</p>\n<p>In definition <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Design_pattern\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Design pattern   Wikipedia</a></p>\n<p>A design pattern is the re-usable form of a solution to a design problem.</p>\n<h2 id=\"what-is-mvc\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#what-is-mvc\" aria-label=\"what is mvc permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>What is MVC?</h2>\n<p>MVC(Model View Controller) is one of the popular design pattern.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>model :  applicationâ€™s data objects are stored</li>\n<li>view : User Interface</li>\n<li>controller: decision maker which is linked between model and view, such as clicking</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"conclusion\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#conclusion\" aria-label=\"conclusion permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Conclusion</h1>\n<p>Hope it helps you to understand MVC. Happy Coding</p>","fields":{"slug":"posts/simple calculator in javascript using MVC pattern","tagSlugs":["/tag/java-script/","/tag/mvc/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2019-12-26T01:31:00.000Z","description":"Simple calculator in javascript using MVC pattern","tags":["JavaScript","MVC"],"title":"Simple calculator in javascript using MVC pattern"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"posts/simple calculator in javascript using MVC pattern"}},"staticQueryHashes":["251939775","401334301","997946461"]}